record_data.record_plain_text:
Marina Energy, LLC Market-Based Rate Tariff
Availability: Marina Energy, LLC ("Marina" or "Seller") makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below.
Applicability: This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by Marina not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Marina.
Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement the purchaser and Marina.
Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Marina.
Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariffor otherwise restricts or limits Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
Seller Category: Seller is a Category 1 seller in the Southwest Power Pool region, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a) and a Category 2 seller in the Northeast, Northwest, Southeast, Southwest, and Central regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a).
7. Limitations and Exemptions, Waivers and Blanket Authorizations: (a) Limitations: Not applicable. (b) Marina has been granted waiver of the following Commission Regulations: (i) Subparts B and C of Part 35 (regarding the filing of rate schedules), except Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; (ii) Part 41 (regarding accounts, records and memoranda); (iii) Part 101 (regarding the Uniform System of Accounts), with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects; and Part 141 (regarding statements and reports). Marina Energy, LLC, Docket No. ER03-715-000, Letter Order at 1 (June 17, 2003) (unpublished letter order). (c) Marina has been granted blanket authorization under Part 34 of the Commission's Regulations for issuances of securities and assumptions of liabilities.

record_data.record_plain_text:
Marina Energy, LLC Market-Based Rate Tariff
1. Availability: Marina Energy, LLC ("Marina" or "Seller") makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited in the balancing authority area of El Paso Electric Company ("EPE") as described further below.
2. Applicability: This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by Marina not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Marina.
3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement the purchaser and Marina.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Marina.
5. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
6. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 1 seller in the Southwest Power Pool region, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a) and a Category 2 seller in the Northeast, Northwest, Southeast, Southwest, and Central regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a).
7. Limitations and Exemptions, Waivers and Blanket Authorizations: (a) Limitations: Not applicable. (b) Marina has been granted waiver of the following Commission Regulations: (i) Subparts B and C of Part 35 (regarding the filing of rate schedules), except Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; (ii) Part 41 (regarding accounts, records and memoranda); (iii) Part 101 (regarding the Uniform System of Accounts), with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects; and Part 141 (regarding statements and reports). Marina Energy, LLC, Docket No. ER03-715-000, Letter Order at 1 (June 17, 2003) (unpublished letter order). (c) Marina has been granted blanket authorization under Part 34 of the Commission's Regulations for issuances of securities and assumptions of liabilities. (d) Seller may not make sales of capacity, energy, and/or ancillary services within the balancing authority area of EPE, where EPE does not have market-based rate authority for sales within its balancing authority area. See El Paso Electric Company, 87 FERC 61,219 (1999); Mankato Energy Center, LLC, et al., 185 FERC 61,134 (2023).
8. Mitigated Sales: Sales of energy and capacity are permissible under this tariff in all balancing authority areas where the Seller has been granted market-based rate authority. Sales of energy and capacity under this tariff are also permissible at the metered boundary between the Seller's mitigated balancing authority area (the EPE balancing authority area) and a balancing authority area where the Seller has been granted market-based rate authority provided: (i) legal title of the power sold transfers at the metered boundary of the balancing authority area where the Seller has market-based rate authority; and (ii) if the Seller sells at the metered boundary of a mitigated balancing authority area at market-based rates, then neither it nor its affiliates can sell into that mitigated balancing authority area from the outside. Seller must retain, for a period of five years from the date of the sale, all data and information related to the sale that demonstrates compliance with items (i) and (ii) above.
9. Effective Date: This Tariff is effective on such date as set by the Commission.
